Sure! Let me review the code carefully for bugs and improvements.

Here's what I've spotted:

🐛 Bugs:

heuristic_score crashes if sender is empty — sender.lower() will fail if the field is blank (e.g., no .eml uploaded and user didn't type anything).
AI score regex is too greedy — re.search(r"\d+", ai_result) grabs the first number in the response, which could be something other than the score (e.g., a year, port number, etc.). It should look specifically for the score line.
PDF text overflow — Long AI responses or URLs will overflow off the page since there's no line wrapping or page break logic in generate_report.
URL regex too greedy — r'(https?://[^\s]+)' captures trailing punctuation like periods or commas as part of the URL.
.eml fields overwrite manual inputs silently — If a user typed something manually and then uploads a file, their input is overwritten with no warning.
⚠️ Improvements:

No input validation — The "Analyze Email" button runs even if all fields are empty.
AbuseIPDB key missing silently — If ABUSE_KEY is None, the API call will fail with a cryptic error.
heuristic_score typo check is hardcoded — Only checks for paypa1, making it very limited.
